Protocol/Guidelines for our first home football game Friday, September 4th vs Winside.

- Kickoff - 7:00
- Masks are REQUIRED if you choose to sit in the bleachers, visit the concession stand, or use the restrooms.
- There are areas surrounding the field that have been labeled "Home Lawn Chair Seating Only" or "Away Lawn Chair Seating Only."
- We encourage all fans to bring lawn chairs and utilize the amount of open space we have for SOCIAL DISTANCING.
- PLEASE do NOT stand along the fence, find a place to stay seated and distanced so you aren't blocking others view of the game.

post_text: Cedar Bluffs Public School is experiencing technical difficulties with our new fire alarm system and therefore by order of the Fire Marshal we will need to limit access to the Community Wellness Center to times when we have employees in the building. Starting Monday August 31, 2020 the Community Wellness Center will only be open Monday through Friday from 4:30am until 11:30pm and No Holidays until we are able to correct the issues with our automated fire alarm system. We are sorry for any inconvenience this may cause.

post_text:
Welcome Back! Below are some reminders for your students regarding riding the bus this school year:

Pick up and drop off times for each route/location for 2020-2021 School Year can be found on the attached document.
Masks are required to ride the bus. Temporary masks are available on the bus for the first day only.
Hand sanitizer is available on the buses when boarding.
Siblings must sit together to assist in spacing students out on the bus.
Buses are sanitized between each usage.
Students are assigned a specific bus and must ride their designated bus in the morning as well as the afternoons.
Parents, please be conscientious when dropping students off in the morning and being on time to pick students up in the afternoon.

If you have any questions regarding bussing arrangements, please contact the director of transportation.
Have a safe and wonderful school year!
https://5il.co/jeq5

Cedar Bluffs Public Schools is requiring all parents to complete E-Registration. E-Registration is an online
tool linked to PowerSchool. E-Registration will be used to update student demographic information,
viewing and approving student handbooks, medical emergency information, and electronic permissions.
In order to start the process parents must have a PowerSchool Parent Account. Parents have the ability to link multiple student accounts together and access the account via one login and password. If you should have any questions please reach out to our secretaries in the HS office or elementary. We would like this to be done as soon as possible!

If you need your student ID or access codes please contact the school during business hours or email Felicia.roumph@cbwildcats.org for that info.

You can find the instructions flyer here: https://5il.co/jc04

post_text:
Dear Families,
Many larger districts are releasing their tentative return to school plans regarding their new Covid procedures and requirements. We too have tentative plans for our return and in many cases are very similar to what is being released. We will be releasing our blueprint after our July 13 school board meeting after the board gives input and hopefully initial approval. At present time, we can say we plan on an Aug. 12 start with 100 percent capacity, while implementing protective health measures. In the meantime, if you have not yet filled out our parent survey please do as we make decisions to finalize our plans.
